      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:8:48:8",
      "text": [
        " سَمِعْتُ أَبِي يَقُولُ الْعِطْرُ مِنْ سُنَنِ الْمُرْسَلِينَ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "A number of our companions, from Ahmad Bin Abu Abdullah, from Muhammad Bin Ali, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Al-Abbas son of Musa<sup>asws</sup> who said, ‘I heard my father<sup>asws</sup> saying: ‘The perfume is from the Sunnah of the <span class=\"iTxt\">Mursil</span> Prophets<sup>as</sup>’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "8. A number of our people have narrated from Ahmad ibn abu ’Abd Allah from Muhammad ibn Ali from al-‘Abbas ibn Musa who has said the following: I heard my father, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, saying, ‘Al-‘Atr (perfume) is of the Sunnah of the messengers (of Allah).”’ "
        ]
      }
